<span class="header1">CREATIVE BUSINESS</span>
<p>You can be successful in this field if you have a talent and can
manage business matters yourself. This field combines artistic
talent with practical business sense.</p>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Chef</span><br /><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/BC/43009.jpg"
width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Chef" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>If you became a chef, you would use your
creativity to prepare new kinds of dishes or meals for others to
eat. You would work in a kitchen creating new recipes, preparing the
meals, and overseeing the staff.  Creativity is important to a
chef.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>No college degree is needed.  Most chefs learn
their craft at schools called "culinary institutes."  Chefs who do
not train at a culinary institute are put through a tough on-the-job
training program while working in a kitchen at another
job.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The median annual wage of chefs was $43,180 in
May 2016. </blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Illustrator</span><br /><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/BC/43312.jpg"
width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Illustrator" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>Illustrators draw or paint pictures that go with
somebody else's words.  Their goal is to "add to" the appeal or
impact of the words.  Their work can be found in newspapers,
magazines, books, and greeting cards.  It can be found in TV
commercials as well.  As an illustrator, you would be most likely to
find work with an advertising agency or a publishing company.  But
other organizations hire illustrators too.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>Most illustrators have had some post high school
courses. A bachelor's degree from a college, university, or an art
school is a definite advantage.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>According to the job search website, indeed.com, the
	median annual wage of illustrators was $46,844 in February 2018. </blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Interior Designer</span><br /><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/BC/43032.jpg"
width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Interior Designer" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>If you have a "knack" for making a room look its
best, you might become an interior designer. Interior designers help
their clients decorate the inside of homes, offices, and
businesses.  In this job, you would decorate rooms working within a
budget. To do this, you would have to know the best prices on
furniture, drapes, and room accessories.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>You need to complete a three to four-year
program in interior designing.  You may want to join a
professional association to find a job.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The median annual wage of interior designers was
$49,810 in May 2016. </blockquote>

